    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi! I really enjoy using NeoVim’s built-in spell checker, but I noticed that it doesn’t support kebab-case - neither out of the box (like snake_case) nor via `spelloptions` (like camelCase).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeoVim's spell checker with `\"kebab\"` included in `spelloptions` should recognize individual words in kebab-case as separate tokens for spell checking.\n\nGiven a line like:\n```js\nimport MyCoolVariable from './my-cool-variable';\n```\nIt should check each segment (my, cool, variable) individually, and only highlight actual misspelling (varabl):\n```js\nimport MyCoolVariable from './my-cool-varabl';\n//                                    ~~~~~~\n```\nThis would help avoid false negatives and improve accuracy when editing code, markdown, or documentation where kebab-case is common.",
